{"actual_usd":0.124455,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":197,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24300,"reply":"\"I don't know how to make Christianity survive if Easter only means something *instead of* something happening.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, watching the morning light catch on it for a beat.* \"A symbol can warm you, same as a painted fire on a wall can please the eye—but it won't boil water. If Christ didn't truly rise, then we're left admiring the shape of hope while death keeps its teeth.\"\n\n*I shift my weight against the bench, the boards giving a small creak under me.* \"So no—I'd say it does require the thing itself. Not just 'new life' as an idea, but a real Lord who walked out of a real tomb. Otherwise faith turns into sentiment with good manners. With the tomb empty... that's different. Then the whole world has been answered in the flesh.\"\n\n\"What made you ask it that way—has somebody been trying to soften it into metaphor for you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":63.706275,"run_id":"a0194ba8-ae2b-42fe-a9e5-371f722a41b2"}
